description:
1987, Santa Carla, California, The Frog Brothers (with, yes, a little help from the Emerson boys) killed the master vampire, thereby saving their town untold horrors. Or... did they?

In 1990, the Frogs return from a slaying excursion in Washington DC to find their old nemesis, David, has attacked the family comic shop. They thought they'd killed him, so how can he be here?
name: TPB

description: Magic Man is being a giant meanie! All the Princesses wanted was a nice picnic with nothing going on for once, but don't worry! Finn and Jake are here to save the day... or are they? When Magic Man uses his tricks against our favorite heroes, it's up to the Princesses to save the day! This stand-alone issue is definitely a must-have, filled with girl power and emoticons!

Archie's Pals N Gals is a great mini collection of hilarious stories from Archie's past and present! Featuring two great stories, fashion pin-ups, puzzles, games and more. This book is a fantastic starting point for new readers and a great refresher for long time fans!
name: Egology

description: Despite being a zombie, Bill Stokes has become quite good at maintaining his mediocre grade point average, keeping a low profile, and gaining online notoriety as a top competitor in the pro-gaming world. But now, Bill's dad is back! Released on legal technicalities from his insurance fraud sentence, Dad's out to get even with Mom and Bill for exposing his schemes! How is Bill going to keep his and Mom's zombie-ness from being revealed to the world?

This comic is about Super LBJ, which stands for Lyndon B. Johnson, and his cabinet. They form a team which is called G.R.E.A.T. (Group Resigned to End All Treats). They fight against supervillons like the French Gaullefinger (DeGaulle) to Russia's Dr. Nyet (Khrushchev). (Dr. Nyet also refers to the Dr. No James Bond movie that came out in 1962.)

Story

Super LBJ has gone missing and everyone searches for him, but they fail. So Super LBJ must save himself and the world from the duo that's been plotting behind the scenes Bobman and Teddy (named after Robert and Ted Kennedy. A sequel came out that starred Bobman and Teddy.
name: The Great Society Comic Book

deck: Coolest team of cool superheroes the world has ever seen
description:
A one-shot comic magazine that was one big commercial. The Ice Team, consisting of Wall's Ice Cream brand people that originally started of as popsicle or lollies. The leader is Sparkle, she comes in lemon or orange flavor, then Twister who tastes like lemon and pineapple and 'Orrible Ogre is blackcurrant.

The Ice Team come to earth in their spaceship called 'Lol-E-Stix' to tackle melding ice-caps and other seemingly natural disasters. It isn't global warming, it's Aunty Freeze's heat rays. She's at the North-Pole with her red devils called 'Hot-Lippers'. the story has a surprise in store for the readers at the end as the Hot-Lippers are not what they seem.

The comic is 16 pages long and in full color. The middle has a pull out poster (see image) of our heroes with their matching ice creams.
Translates : Dark Avengers/Uncanny X-Men: Utopia, Exodus, Uncanny X-Men 513-514, Dark Avengers #07-08 , Dark X-Men: The Confession
name: Patrulla-X Vs. Vengadores Oscuros: Utopía

volume.name: Hanna-Barbera's Wheelie and the Chopper Bunch

description: Doom on the moon! Doctor Doom has used his magic to imprison Tony after stripping him of his armor during their battle in the moontown of Prosperity Gulch. But is this really the end for the Iron Man?
Lois is worried that a bored Chloe won’t last long in her Metropolis visit, but she’s got the perfect field trip planned: there’s something going down in Gotham!
name: Chapter Four

description: While Zod adjusts to his new life on Earth, strange things begin to happen within the new Justice League Watchtower…
name: System Override, Part 1 of 8: Color Wheel of Doom

description:
It's the second issue of the new Weekly Shonen Jump! We hope you're enjoying the new look and feel of the magazine, as well as the brand new addition to the lineup, One-Punch Man! In this special origin chapter, he takes on the brutal crab-man-thing, Crablante, whose catchphrase "Gurgle-borgle" will no doubt soon be taking America by storm! Also in this issue, we're running Kintoki - a special one-shot by Dragon Ball Z creator, the legendary Akira Toriyama. And in Toriko, the evil Gourmet Corp. has made their move and Toriko and the other Four Kings are in for the fight of their life! All this and a whole lot more!
